<<<<<How to Run>>>>>

  ================================================================================
    QUICK START
  ================================================================================
    apptainer run --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/output:/output container.sif jupyter

  (CPU-only — no --nv / --rocm needed. `import mlflow` works out of the box.)


  ================================================================================
    MODES & FLAGS
  ================================================================================
    MODES
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
      jupyter (default)   JupyterLab, import mlflow works out of the box
        apptainer run --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/output:/output \
          container.sif jupyter

      mlflow               MLflow tracking server + UI only
        apptainer run --bind /my/output:/output container.sif mlflow

      jupyter+mlflow        Both at once (server in background, Jupyter in foreground)
        apptainer run --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/output:/output \
          container.sif jupyter+mlflow

    FLAGS
    --------------------------------------------------------------------------
      --bind src:dst     --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/output:/output
      --env KEY=VALUE    --env MLFLOW_PORT=5001

    Directories to bind: /code /data /output (mlflow.db + artifacts/ land here) /model /scratch


  ================================================================================
    RUN YOUR OWN SCRIPT (EXEC)
  ================================================================================
    # Train — logs to MLflow via /output automatically
    apptainer exec \
      --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/data:/data --bind /my/output:/output \
      container.sif python /code/train.py

    # Inspect runs without starting the full server
    apptainer exec --bind /my/output:/output container.sif mlflow runs list


  ================================================================================
    SLURM — SINGLE NODE
  ================================================================================
    #!/bin/bash
    #SBATCH --job-name=classical-ml-mlflow-train
    #SBATCH --cpus-per-task=8
    #SBATCH --mem=32G
    #SBATCH --partition=cpu
    #SBATCH --output=./logs/logs_%j.out
    #SBATCH --error=./logs/logs_%j.err
    #SBATCH --time=02:00:00

    echo "===================================="
    echo "Job Name   : $SLURM_JOB_NAME"
    echo "CPUs       : $SLURM_CPUS_PER_TASK"
    echo "===================================="

    srun apptainer exec \
      --bind /my/code:/code --bind /my/data:/data --bind /my/output:/output \
      container.sif python /code/train.py

    echo "===================================="
    echo "Training Completed"
    echo "===================================="

    No multi-node section — single-process, single-node by design. Each job's
    /output bind gets its own mlflow.db. For one tracking server shared across
    several jobs instead:
      srun apptainer run --bind /my/output:/output container.sif mlflow &
      export MLFLOW_TRACKING_URI=http://<server-node>:5000
    Find <server-node> with: squeue -j <jobid> -o "%N"


  ================================================================================
    CHECKING IT WORKS
  ================================================================================
    apptainer test container.sif

